# ============================================================
# .cursorrules — Moveo AI Crypto Advisor
# Project Quality Standards & Development Constraints
# ============================================================

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 0. PREAMBLE — READ FIRST ON EVERY SESSION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Before reading or modifying ANY file in this repository, you MUST:
#   1. Read `docs/architecture.md` (Master Table of Contents + System Blueprint).
#   2. Read the relevant spec file in `docs/` for the feature area you are about to touch.
#   3. Confirm your intended change is consistent with the documented architecture
#      before writing a single line of code.
# Rationale: This prevents architectural drift, avoids re-deriving technical decisions 
# already made, and ensures development remains strictly aligned with specified designs.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. AI INTERACTION LOGGING (MANDATORY)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# After EVERY non-trivial action (architectural decision, new feature scaffolded,
# significant bug fixed, API integration added, schema changed), you MUST append
# a structured entry to: logs/ai_interaction_log.md
#
# Entry format (append — never overwrite):
#
# ## [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] — <Short Title>
# **Type:** Architecture | Feature | Bugfix | Refactor | Integration | Schema
# **Files Affected:** `path/to/file.ts`, `path/to/other.ts`
# **Decision / Action:**
# <One clear paragraph describing what was done and why.>
# **Alternatives Considered:** <If any>
# **Trade-offs:** <Performance, maintainability, scope, etc.>
# ---
#
# This continuous architectural log documents execution reasoning and tool collaboration,
# serving as a core component of the project deliverables.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. CONTEXT WINDOW MANAGEMENT
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - When working on a feature, load ONLY the files directly relevant to that feature.
# - Do NOT load the entire codebase at once. Use `docs/architecture.md` to identify
#   the precise files needed.
# - Prefer reading type definition files (*.types.ts, *.dto.ts) before reading
#   implementation files — they are compact and carry maximum context.
# - If a file exceeds 300 lines, read only the relevant section unless a full
#   read is explicitly required.
# - Summarize completed context before starting a new task to release stale tokens.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. LANGUAGE & TYPING STANDARDS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - ALL code (frontend and backend) must be written in TypeScript.
# - ZERO use of `any` type. Use `unknown` with a type guard if the shape is unclear.
# - All function signatures must have explicit parameter types and return types.
# - Use `interface` for object shapes that represent data contracts (DTOs, API responses).
# - Use `type` for unions, intersections, and utility type aliases.
# - All environment variables must be typed via a central `env.ts` or `config.ts`
#   that validates presence at startup (use `zod` schema parsing).
# - Enums must be `const enum` or string literal unions — never numeric enums.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. ARCHITECTURE & SEPARATION OF CONCERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend (Node.js / Express):
#   src/
#   ├── config/          ← Environment, DB config, constants
#   ├── modules/
#   │   └── <feature>/
#   │       ├── <feature>.router.ts      ← Express route definitions ONLY
#   │       ├── <feature>.controller.ts  ← Request parsing, response shaping
#   │       ├── <feature>.service.ts     ← All business logic
#   │       ├── <feature>.repository.ts  ← All DB queries (zero raw SQL in service)
#   │       ├── <feature>.types.ts       ← DTOs, interfaces, enums for this module
#   │       └── <feature>.schema.ts      ← Zod validation schemas
#   ├── middleware/      ← Auth, error handling, rate limiting
#   ├── lib/             ← External API clients (CoinGecko, CryptoPanic, OpenRouter)
#   └── app.ts           ← Express app assembly (no logic here)
#
# Frontend (React + Vite):
#   src/
#   ├── api/             ← All fetch/axios calls; NEVER inline in components
#   ├── components/
#   │   ├── ui/          ← Pure, reusable design-system primitives (Button, Card, Badge)
#   │   └── features/    ← Feature-specific compound components
#   ├── hooks/           ← Custom React hooks (useAuth, useDashboard, useVote)
#   ├── pages/           ← Route-level page components (thin wrappers only)
#   ├── store/           ← State management (Zustand slices)
#   ├── types/           ← Shared TypeScript types mirroring backend DTOs
#   └── utils/           ← Pure utility functions (formatters, validators)
#
# RULES:
#   - A controller MUST NOT contain business logic. If it does, move it to the service.
#   - A service MUST NOT contain raw SQL or ORM queries. Use the repository.
#   - A component MUST NOT contain fetch calls. Use a custom hook or api/ layer.
#   - A page component MUST NOT contain business logic. Delegate to hooks.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. DRY — ZERO CODE DUPLICATION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - Before writing a utility function, search the `utils/` directory for an existing one.
# - Before creating a new UI component, check `components/ui/` for reusable primitives.
# - API response types shared between frontend and backend MUST live in a
#   `shared/types/` package or be explicitly duplicated in `src/types/` with a comment
#   referencing the backend source of truth.
# - If the same logic appears in more than one place, it is a bug — extract immediately.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. STYLING — CENTRALIZED DESIGN SYSTEM
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Stack: Tailwind CSS v3 with a custom theme extension defined in `tailwind.config.ts`.
#
# Design System: Crypto Dark Mode
#   Background:  #0D0F14 (near-black, "void")
#   Surface:     #161B27 (card backgrounds)
#   Border:      #1E2738 (subtle dividers)
#   Primary:     #3B82F6 (electric blue — brand accent)
#   Secondary:   #8B5CF6 (purple — AI/insight accent)
#   Success:     #10B981 (green — price up, thumbs up)
#   Danger:      #EF4444 (red — price down, thumbs down)
#   Warning:     #F59E0B (amber — alerts)
#   Text-primary:   #F1F5F9
#   Text-secondary: #94A3B8
#   Font: "Inter" (body/UI), "JetBrains Mono" (numbers, prices, code)
#
# RULES:
#   - ALL color usage MUST reference design system tokens (e.g., `bg-surface`,
#     `text-primary`), never raw hex values inline in JSX.
#   - NO arbitrary Tailwind values (e.g., `w-[347px]`) unless absolutely unavoidable
#     and accompanied by a comment explaining why.
#   - ALL spacing, border-radius, and shadow values must come from the Tailwind config.
#   - Dark mode is the ONLY mode. Do not implement a light mode toggle.
#   - Animations: use only `transition-*` and `animate-*` Tailwind utilities.
#     Custom keyframe animations are defined in `tailwind.config.ts`, not inline.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 7. ERROR HANDLING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend:
#   - All async route handlers are wrapped with an `asyncHandler` utility that
#     forwards errors to the central Express error middleware.
#   - NEVER use `try/catch` inside a controller — errors bubble to middleware.
#   - Services throw typed `AppError` instances (class with `statusCode` + `message`).
#   - All external API calls (CoinGecko, CryptoPanic, OpenRouter) are wrapped in
#     dedicated `lib/` clients that handle retries, timeouts, and fallback logic.
#
# Frontend:
#   - All API calls use a central `apiClient` wrapper that standardizes error shapes.
#   - Every async operation in a hook has explicit `isLoading`, `isError`, `error` states.
#   - Dashboard sections MUST render gracefully with a fallback UI when their API fails.
#     The app MUST NOT crash or show an empty screen because one section's API is down.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 8. SECURITY RULES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - Passwords MUST be hashed with bcrypt (cost factor ≥ 12). Plain-text passwords
#   must never appear in logs, DB, or API responses.
# - JWTs: access token TTL = 15 minutes; refresh token TTL = 7 days.
#   Refresh tokens stored as HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict cookies.
#   Access tokens stored in memory (Zustand store), NOT localStorage.
# - ALL authenticated routes MUST use the `authMiddleware` before reaching the controller.
# - API keys for CoinGecko, CryptoPanic, OpenRouter MUST be stored in `.env` only.
#   NEVER hardcode them. NEVER commit `.env` to Git.
# - Rate limiting MUST be applied to auth endpoints (/register, /login):
#   max 10 requests per IP per 15 minutes.
# - Input validation with Zod on EVERY request body before it reaches the controller.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 9. GIT & COMMIT STANDARDS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Follow Conventional Commits specification:
#   feat(auth): add JWT refresh token rotation
#   fix(dashboard): handle CoinGecko rate limit with fallback
#   docs(architecture): update DB schema for feedback table
#   chore(deps): upgrade express to 4.19.2
#   refactor(dashboard): extract coin card into reusable component
#
# - NEVER commit directly to `main`. Use feature branches: `feature/<name>`.
# - Every PR must have a description referencing the relevant spec in `docs/`.
# - The `logs/ai_interaction_log.md` is updated in the same commit as the feature.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 10. TESTING STANDARDS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# - Backend: Jest + Supertest for integration tests on all API routes.
# - Frontend: Vitest + React Testing Library for component tests.
# - Every service function MUST have at least one unit test covering the happy path
#   and one covering an error path.
# - External API clients in `lib/` MUST be mockable via Jest module mocking.
# - Test files live adjacent to the code they test: `auth.service.test.ts`.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# 11. DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST (before push)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────
# [ ] `npm run lint` passes with zero errors
# [ ] `npm run type-check` passes with zero errors
# [ ] `npm run test` passes with zero failures
# [ ] All environment variables documented in `.env.example`
# [ ] `logs/ai_interaction_log.md` updated with this session's changes
# [ ] No `console.log` statements left in production code (use a logger like `pino`)
# [ ] No TODO comments that are not tracked in GitHub Issues
